===en-us-ap (Appalachian English)===
<!-- NOTE: Before deleting this table as "insulting" or because "nobody talks like that," please note: 
- These boxes reflect a dialect spoken by some people in the Appalachian mountains, not by everyone who lives in the Appalachian region of the United States. You are not an expert on Appalachian English just because you live in AL, GA, KY, NC, SC, PA, TN, VA, or WV. 
- People who talk like this are not inferior, and representing their speech is not an act of hatred. 
- The spelling used here is based on the spelling used by professional linguists who take the dialect seriously. See, e.g. http://lowlands-l.net/appalachian.php
- Please consider improving the boxes by editing, or discussing your concerns on the relevant talk page. 
- Users have put these boxes on their user pages, so think twice before deleting them. Thanks. 
-->{{Language table|en-us-ap}}

